									net amount
								</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td >
									course fee</span>
								</td>
								<td>
									&euro; 5,950.-
								</td>
								<td class="net">
									&euro; 5,000.00
								</td>
							</tr>
<!-- 							<tr>
								<td >
									Apply and confirm by <span class="strong">January 9</span>
								</td>
								<td>
									&euro; 6,200.-
								</td>
								<td class="net">
									&euro; 5,210.08
								</td>
							</tr> -->
							<tr id="scholarship">
								<td >
									partial scholarship*
								</td>
								<td colspan="2">
									./. &euro; 350.00
								</td>
							</tr>
						</table>
					</div> <!-- end csstable -->
					<p class="subtext">* We offer a <span class="strong">partial scholarship</span> to female participants and non-EU and first-generation immigrants from certain countries - people we would like to become much more visible in tech.</p>

					<p><span class="strong">A down payment of &euro; 1,000.- will reserve your spot and is due at the latest 7 days prior to the course.</span></p>
					<p>The remainder of the tuition is payable within 7 days of the course. We also offer a payment plan after the down payment, with a first installment of &euro; 2,300 due within 7 days of the course start and two installments of &euro; 1,500 each at eight and sixteen weeks after the course end (total &euro; 6,300.- incl. VAT). <br>
					Please contact us if you have any question regarding tuition and payment plan.</p>
					<p>We will supply an invoice for the tuition. The VAT charge can be omitted for businesses and sole proprietors, both from EU and non-EU countries.</p>

				</div> <!-- end coursentry -->
			</div>



			<div class="twelve columns">
				<div class="faqentry">
					<h2 class="category">The courses</h2>
					<h3 class="faqheading">Who is behind Stackademy?</h3>
					<div class="text jus">
						<p>We are a small outfit, run by technology enthusiasts that is based in Berlin. Together with great developers, we jointly create intense programs with a focus
						on practice - let us know if you are interested in teaching a course with us and become a part of <span class="strong">Stackademy</span>.
						<br />More about us on our <a href="about.html">About us</a> page.</p>
					</div>
					<p><a href="#top" class="toplink anchorLink"><span class="entypo">8</span> back to top</a></p>
				</div> <!-- end faqentry -->

				<div class="faqentry" id="teaching">
					<h3 class="faqheading">So who is teaching?</h3>
					<div class="text jus">
						<p>All of our instructors are developers with years of experience, who are on top of trends and developments in their field through practical
						work and real-world projects. Whenever we can work out a course with them, we make sure all the parameters fit to make the program the intense and
						rewarding learning experience you are looking for. You can find out more about the individual instructor on the course page</p>
					</div>
					<p><a href="#top" class="toplink anchorLink"><span class="entypo">8</span> back to top</a></p>
				</div> <!-- end faqentry -->

				<div class="faqentry" id="forme">
					<h3 class="faqheading">Is this for me?</h3>
					<div class="text jus">
						<p>All of the <span class="strong">Stackademy</span> courses are designed to get you ready for more in the most intense way possible.
						If we require previous programming experience, you can find a note on the course page, but in general, motivation and dedication make the difference.</p>
						<p>Can you work through a book or an online course instead? Most certainly. In our experience, however, we have found that the results of a full-time
						course far exceed what you're likely to pick up through a self-paced course in less time. Additionally, we work hard to bring in the right partners for each course, making it much easier for you to take the next steps after graduation.</p>
						<p>That being said, a great and up-to-date resource we recommend for beginners as well as for our students is the <a href="http://learn-rails.com/learn-ruby-on-rails.html">Learn Ruby on Rails</a> book.</p>
						<p>For additional online courses, check out <a href="http://careerfoundry.com">CareerFoundry</a>, a mentor-assisted online course and <a href="http://onemonthrails.com">OneMonthRails</a>, and contact us for special rates.</p>
					</div>
					<p><a href="#top" class="toplink anchorLink"><span class="entypo">8</span> back to top</a></p>
				</div> <!-- end faqentry -->

				<div class="faqentry">
					<h3 class="faqheading">How does the Recruiting Day work?</h3>
					<div class="text jus">
						<p>For all of our programs, we work with companies that are interested in getting to know the <span class="strong">Stackademy</span> graduates. We don't guarantee a placement, but
						if you pass a partner's application process and stay on after the trial phase, we will refund EUR 1,000 (incl. tax) of your tuition.</p>
						<p>We have made sure to only bring in companies that we know personally. We also include excursions to the offices of some of our partners, so that you can learn more yourself and get in
						touch with the development team. And of course, you are free to choose an entirely different career path for yourself.</p>
					</div>
					<p><a href="#top" class="toplink anchorLink"><span class="entypo">8</span> back to top</a></p>
				</div> <!-- end faqentry -->

				<div class="faqentry">
					<h3 class="faqheading">"Unique courses" - what's the deal?</h3>
					<div class="text jus">
						<p>At <span class="strong">Stackademy</span>, we want every course to be the best it can be. To achieve that, we look for experienced developers and find a suitable time for them to
						teach a course that really fits their profile. As our instructors continue to work for companies and on projects, we currently only run a program when
						the right instructor is on board to teach. If you want to be the first to hear about new courses, sign up for our <a href="http://eepurl.com/yvsYz" title="Newsletter signup" target="_blank">free newsletter</a>.</p>
					</div>
					<p><a href="#top" class="toplink anchorLink"><span class="entypo">8</span> back to top</a></p>
				</div> <!-- end faqentry -->

				<div class="faqentry">
					<h3 class="faqheading">How long are the courses exactly?</h3>
					<div class="text jus">
						<p><span class="strong">Stackademy Web Application Development</span> runs for 12 weeks from 9am to 6pm (or longer if you're in the zone and want to stay).</p>
						<p>Additionally, we provide basic prep material to all participants to work through before the start of the course, which you can complete anywhere where you have an internet connection - and we're available in case of questions.</p>
						<p>For the duration of the actual courses, you shouldn't have any other major commitments to attend to. We don't chain anyone to their desk but you'll want to be able to commit to making the most
						out of the course. It'll be worth it.</p>
					</div>
					<p><a href="#top" class="toplink anchorLink"><span class="entypo">8</span> back to top</a></p>
				</div> <!-- end faqentry -->

				<div class="faqentry">
					<h3 class="faqheading">Do I need to bring a laptop?</h3>
					<div class="text jus">
						<p>Yes, we do recommend that. While we provide iMac workstations with all necessary applications, you benefit from having your own system to work on for homework and personal exercises.<br />
						We can provide a loaner laptop if this is an issue for you.</p>
					</div>
					<p><a href="#top" class="toplink anchorLink"><span class="entypo">8</span> back to top</a></p>
				</div> <!-- end faqentry -->

				<div class="faqentry">
					<h3 class="faqheading">Is Stackademy a certified course?</h3>
					<div class="text jus">
						<p><span class="strong">Stackademy</span> currently is not certified by a third party. In our experience, good companies will base their hiring decisions for technical positions on actual
						development skills, and we make sure you're prepared as superbly as possible for that. You might also be surprised how many certified CS graduates aren't
						familiar with developing actual applications, and we haven't seen a solution that would allow us to solve this, other than offering a kick-ass course.</p>
						<p>In addition, we provide you with course documentation on your skills and achievements upon completion of the course.</p>
					</div>
					<p><a href="#top" class="toplink anchorLink"><span class="entypo">8</span> back to top</a></p>
				</div> <!-- end faqentry -->
			</div>

